    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" ns:sid="2047271448391774209" ns:tid="2047271794452148225" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="52">
        <source>Why Is the Battery Power Not Used Up on the Same Day?</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" ns:sid="2047271448391774210" ns:tid="2047271794452148226" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>Cross-period economic optimization</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" ns:sid="2047271448391774211" ns:tid="2047271794452148227" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="57">
        <source>The <ph id="f0">&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph1959151418587&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;</ph> dynamically schedules battery charge and discharge based on AI algorithms that forecast load, PV output, and electricity prices.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" ns:sid="2047271448391774212" ns:tid="2047271794452148228" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="31">
        <source>The system reserves some energy for discharge during <bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b853053116521&quot;&gt;</bpt>periods with higher electricity prices on the next day<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept> to maximize the returns from energy arbitrage.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" ns:sid="2047271448391774213" ns:tid="2047271794452148229" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="43">
        <source>If the battery is fully discharged on the current day, better arbitrage opportunities on the next day may be missed.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" ns:sid="2047271448391774214" ns:tid="2047271794452148230" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>Active response to negative electricity prices</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" ns:sid="2047271448391774215" ns:tid="2047271794452148231" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b205301631145211&quot;&gt;</bpt>Charging first<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" ns:sid="2047271448391774216" ns:tid="2047271794452148232" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="58">
        <source>When the electricity price is negative (the purchase price is negative), the system preferentially purchases electricity from the grid for charging.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" ns:sid="2047271448391774217" ns:tid="2047271794452148233" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>In this case, the battery may be in the charging state instead of the discharging state.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" ns:sid="2047271448391774218" ns:tid="2047271794452148234" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b1953016313528&quot;&gt;</bpt>Policy adjustment<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" ns:sid="2047271448391774219" ns:tid="2047271794452148235" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="40">
        <source>After the negative rate optimization function is enabled, the battery proactively charges during low electricity price periods (including negative electricity prices) to reduce the discharge amount.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" ns:sid="2047271448391774220" ns:tid="2047271794452148236" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>SOC protection and backup power requirements</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="13" ns:sid="2047271448391774221" ns:tid="2047271794452148237" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="37">
        <source>The system sets the end-of-discharge SOC (for example, 50%) to prevent overdischarge and battery damage, and reserves <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol18815162434613&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784935935.xml#460689&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784935935&quot;/&gt;</ph> to cope with unexpected power outages.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14" ns:sid="2047271448391774222" ns:tid="2047271794452148238" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="41">
        <source>The <ph id="f0">&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph15116442102016&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;</ph> dynamically adjusts the discharge threshold based on the power backup requirements.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15" ns:sid="2047271448391774223" ns:tid="2047271794452148239" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>Power and load matching</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="16" ns:sid="2047271448391774224" ns:tid="2047271794452148240" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="45">
        <source>If the load demand is lower than the battery's discharge power, the system adjusts the discharge output accordingly to avoid energy waste.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="17" ns:sid="2047271448391774225" ns:tid="2047271794452148241" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="42">
        <source>For example, during light-load periods, the battery supplies only part of the power, with the remaining charge reserved for future use.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
